HEADWORD: Strongyloid
<hw>Stron"gy*loid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Strongylus</ets> the genus (from Gr. <?/ round) +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Like, or pertaining to,
<gen>Strongylus</gen>, a genus of parasitic nematode worms of which many
species infest domestic animals. Some of the species, especially those
living in the kidneys, lungs, and bronchial tubes, are often very
injurious.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A strongyloid
worm.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

